DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: In zoology, denoting the sex that bears the young or the ovum._The capacity to conceive or to induce conception. It may refer to either the male or female._An indication that a person has a condition or disease.  Some examples of symptoms are headache, fever, fatigue, nausea, vomiting, and pain._Past; before the present time._One of the 12 divisions of a year as determined by a calendar.  It corresponds to the unit of time of approximately to one cycle of the moon's phases, about 30 days or 4 weeks._Occurrence; an instance of something happening._Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.
